caption: This spot sure knows how to please their clients. Always with a super nice demeanor. The food is conveniently priced, regularly tasty and neat.
The tables right next to the kitchen counter and front door aren't ideal if you want to be able to hold a conversation
Over priced, crowed and average food

Service is great, food is solid. I come here at least once a week for a business lunch. Fish and chips are surprisingly really good. I usually go with a salad. Flash fried Brussel sprouts are really good.
Very friendly staff. Good happy hour before the opera. $8 wine. $10 flat bread or loaded fries. The Midwest Cobb salad is really good. They use high quality chicken.
Typical American food

Due to its location across Wacker from the Lyric Opera, we have probably eaten here more than any other restaurant in Chicago over the past 10+ years. The Saturday night opera menu has something for everyone and bigger than the regular menu of many restaurants. The food quality is always excellent. Service can be variable but recent visits have shown a great amount of teamwork among the staff, and you have to admire how this team always gets you out in plenty of time to make it to your seat at the opera. It’s a lovely space to enjoy a meal.
Good place for business lunch.
Service and food were meh. Would love to see this place step up their game now that Lloyd's is no more.
Nice place. Good food....pricey
Very efficient wait staff. Food was good. Not conversation friendly. Not a warm atmosphere re the decor.
The food was good. Healthy options. Friendly waitstaff.
Best white fish

The meal of the day was very good.
Excellent food and service I would go back again
Great food here very nice atmosphere

This place has a nice enough ambience. The last few weeks I visited about 3 or 4 times. If you're sitting on one of the tables in the bar area they were using 2 waitresses and each seemed to be confused what the other one was told or knew about our table. So it was more interruption than I would have liked.  Food is okay. Very standard American food. The loop generally does not have any restaurants in the south area that surpass the quality scale for food. They are all short of great in taste and quality. Not a bad thing but due to the constant tourist and work influx, none of these places seem to have the motivation to kick things up a notch.
Great loop lunch, good food and really speedy service
Good, solid and quick lunch.  Tasty ceasar was great!!
Delicious
Great food, excellent service!

This was our 3rd time here in this place because they have buratta but our order this time has a lot of carcinogens! The bread that comes with the buratta was burned! The patty was burned and not well cooked in the middle (I requested medium well). The bread that comes with the buratta was burned, so we requested a new slice of bread because we couldn't enjoy the buratta cheese (appetizer) if all you got to taste was carcinogens! The service was good. Waiters and the bar tender was very nice. The grilled cheese we ordered was delicious (they didn't burn that one). We sat by the bar and the Atmosphere there was classy and sporty as you got to watch soccer games in tv. Everything would have been perfect yesterday if the food was not burned. We don't like to pay  and all we got to eat was carcinogens or burned food (which is bad for you by the way because it can cause cancer). Please see attached pictures.
Great place for quick bites and drinks. Food was delicious and they had really nice cocktails.

All food was burnt to a crisp—every item on the table. When we told the waiter, he laughed. Some entrees were served wrong. Getting the bills took 30 minutes and was a disaster. Some cards were charged twice. Horrible place, horrible service. Do not recommend.

First time there before seeing a show at the Chicago Theater (about a 10 minute walk)...really enjoyed the calamari we had (nice to not have to eat it fried, like just about every place I go to)...the salmon was good and I ate a good amount of the chicken my gf ordered, as well.  I liked the atmosphere...granted, it was before a show on a Saturday.  Nevertheless, it was enjoyable enough to have a drink, appetizer, conversation and a good meal.

We never got past the front desk. We reserved a table at this location and when we arrived, we were told they were too busy and they only had high tops available by the door and kitchen. Over half of the restaurant was empty and they were forcing people into a loud, over crowded seating by the front entrance. The executive chef was assisting seating people and was extremely crass and rude telling people it is what it is. A very sad start to what was supposed to be a nice date night. After the attitude, poor manners and rudeness to not even listen to my request that I reserved a table and not a high top. We left because they were so rude. I will never be back to this place. Rude, rude, rude and put a damper on what was supposed to be a special night.

The food was very tasty.  Bianca was our server. She was very friendly and attentive.  I would have given 5 stars however when they tried to sit our reservation at a high top table and we declined (due to a disability) we were told we requested a high table when we reserved which was totally false.
Great location for a pre-opera meal. Busy place but I foind the noice level very high. The service was generally good but there was a mix-up with the bills. Food was delicious
Tasty food and they validated our parking. Gouda Puffs were really good, as were the Scallops and the burger.
Great food and service. Always enjoy being there.
Very good food. Can get overrun before a show or performance at the Opera House across the street.
We had some great drinks and the Buffalo chicken dirty fries was exacy what a long day of meetings needed to close it out.
Top notch. Thanks Catherine Okoroh for inviting Jaye and I to the 2018 CAR pre-Award bash 😎
Good lunch standby

Best in the area. Great atmosphere, super friendly staff. This place is a hidden treasure. Definitely recommend if you are in this area. The staff is wonderful and the prices are reasonable. Every time the place and its staff treats us so well that One North Kitchen & Bar is the first place that comes to our mind when we have to decide the venue for our parties. Everyone at this place is so cheerful.

Cheddar burgers were burnt at the edges, not cooked on the inside with a density that suggests a lot of filler. Spicing was WAY overdone, as were the fries. Pretzel bun was very soggy way salty. Great service though, especially for an opera night.
Such a great place for after work cocktails. And lunch is good. A bit $$$ but worth it.
Met a friend for drinks here. A bit noisy but expected this on a Friday evening. Nothing special just convenient for after work and friendly service.
Great class food and service see extended comments on open table

This is such an amazing place to grab drinks, lunch, or dinner.  They food is always made with fresh ingredients and they have options for everyone.  Chef Piper puts her heart and soul into her restaurants and you can definitely taste it. This is a great place.
Beautiful,  staff friendly and service is great.  The appetizers amazing (sliders and risotto balls). I loved my scallops and the rest of my party certainly enjoyed their entrees....must so again

Okay, this might be a bit low considering everyone else's experience in the reviews so far, but here's why I'm probably not coming back:  1. I came here on a Friday about 4pm and ordered two of the cheddar burgers. They did not have any taste to them. It felt like they lacked Adobo or any seasoning that night. I ordered medium well and the ends came out super burnt. So with each bite was a burnt taste. I was pretty hungry so I ate it anyway.  The place is a bit pricey and days later I, which I haven't done in years went to get a Whopper with cheese at Burger King. Flavor was amazing and I kicked myself for eating such a bland expensive burger days earlier.  Sometimes the most expensive experience isn't the tastiest.  The drinks were okay. I'm from Pilsen so I probably prefer the bars around here for nice mixed drinks at better prices.  The decor was nice though, no complaints from the service.  But I won't be remembering this place as a place to return to.
Work sponsored Happ Hour.
One of the waitresses melisa was very friendly and nice.. she made sure I was well taken care of.. doesn't happen a lot in chicago..  I made sure to tip her very well...
Burnt burgers and I don't think the cook knows about salt and pepper.

I can recommend this to anyone. The service was amazing and the food you can better. Great place to go before seeing an opera. Keep in mind that they have a different menu for opera nights, so don't bother planning ahead by looking at the menu.
Prices are a bit high, but you can find value. Much more if a lunch/happy hour spot

Nice environment, good food great selection of beer and wine. If youre looking to spend some cash on drinks this is good place to be. It's proximity to the Washington and Wells train station only makes it more appealing.

Had a Holiday business luncheon with 9 people. Food and service were great. Only issue was we were seated at a high-top table, of which there were many. I would have preferred a regular table.

Been here three times for post work drinks. Haven't had their food yet. Three stars bc the service has been average and the venue is on par w what u can expect downtown. Simply fantastic. Went for a company event two years in a row. Great food and service.  They really take care of us.
Not cozy, but great food and service. Interesting menu items.
Food was delicious. Place was festively decorated. Had a great time.

If this is your first time in Chicago, this is probably one of the first places you'll enter. Prices are around the average leaning towards premium range, and the atmosphere was pretty modern. Past the dim lighting, the food is pretty good.  Photo is the Sausage Rigatoni.
Rich and his staff are first class. Whatever you need they will do their best to accommodate you.

Visiting Chicago this past Friday and friends brought us here and it was Wonderful! The most delicious scallops ever, cooked to perfection. But the star of that show was the curry butter, TO DIE FOR! It came with spaghetti squash but because I'm addicted to carbs I asked if they would swap that for polenta and they easily accommodated and happier I could not be as they were tasty and decadent while not being heavy. I saw a girl in a chef outfit so I called her over and she was proud to tell us how the polenta is made locally and female owned. Overall a really nice night. Waiter was also top notch. I'd totally go back. But I'll be here in New York thinking about that dish for a long while!

Chef Laura is amazing and knowledgeable, especially regarding gluten free and what it truly means. She also understands fish allergies and since the fries are cooked in a separate fryer from the fish as well as the gluten containing items, I could enjoy french fries for the first time in years! Great food and staff.

Felt that the price was a little higher than the usual but the food was great. They have a pretty big area of outdoor seating which is great for those nice summer evenings. As it's in the loop, it would make a great spot to have lunch with your teammates and catch up. Really liked their dessert brownie ice cream with pecans! Yumm 😋

The staff was friendly, helpful and took the initiative.

Went with a girlfriend, but there was enough stuff on the menu to try that I know my husband will also enjoy. The bar area is home to happy hour- which has a separate little menu too. Didn't indulge in dessert this time, but that also looked great (even though I'm not usually a dessert person). good loop spot. pricey of course. bacon risotto is great. get them brussels sprouts outta here
I stopped in for a lunch with coworkers and there was a good table available outside.  The food was served very quickly and BBQ Pulled Chicken sandwich was great.
Best Turkey sandwich in the loop. Just gets busy during lunch.

I dined here last night (1.6.16) with 8 others in my party. As a Celiac and a host of a large group, I hate making a scene about my need to eat gluten-free. One North does not have a dedicated gluten-free menu, but our server was incredibly informative. He mentioned what dishes could be made gluten-free (and he did it with a smile on his face...sometimes get get eye balls rolled in my direction). Anyway, I was ecstatic to find out that the scallops with spaghetti squash could be made for me. To my surprise, the chef personally delivered my gluten-free entree to my table. It was delicious!! I so appreciate her taking my Celiac Disease, seriously and I appreciate the server being informative and kind. 5 STARS...the evening was perfect! Thank you!

The food is pretty good, overall. This is a nice place to bring interview candidates or have working lunches and outings. They have an old style cocktail menu with traditional mixers and a descent beer selection on tap. The design is more upscale and modern, with an ok view out the front.
Overpriced, but it has a decent location

I'd like to first of all start by saying that this comment is almost 5 months overdue as I had the absolute pleasure of having my wedding reception here in October. As a self-proclaimed "laid back perfectionist" (what?), I can say with absolute certainty that having our wedding reception at One North was one of the best choices we made during our wedding planning process. We were taken care of from the minute our initial inquiry was emailed to Jude Abella, the Director of Events/Event Coordinator, to the final touches that we didn't even notice until weeks after the wedding with her saving the corks used for the champagne toast in a box we later opened. Jude made sure every detail - big or small - was successfully executed to a T. Her attention to detail completely exceeded my expectations including, but not limited to, making herself available to us when needed, offering helpful checklists each and every step of the way, staying on top of our vendors and even getting to know us on a personal level to make sure the night was a sincere reflection of us. In an initial discovery period she even found out that my guilty pleasure is... (wait for it) cheese fries. Her and her staff figured out which ones were my favorite in this great city of ours, and One North's phenomenal chef/magician, Laura Piper, recreated them to an even better version of my favorite (sorry 'boutcha DMK) which were then served towards the end of the evening when everyone could use a little fries+cheese+bacon+sour-cream+green-onion action. While I'm on the topic of food, we all know wedding food is historically...not great. So, shame on me for expecting ours to follow suit in the mediocre wedding food category. Chef Piper and Jude worked within our expectations and budget to deliver a few different meal options that were OUTSTANDING (Yes, the caps were necessary.) I can't tell you how many different people stopped me during the reception to sing praises about the food. To quote one of my dad's friends, "I felt like I was at a 5 star restaurant for dinner and a night out in the city". My husband and I are definitely foodies and the meals Chef Piper created and prepared were flavorful, fresh, unique, gorgeous and delicious. The rest of the management staff and waitstaff were professional and ‘on it’. The cocktails were not that of what you'd expect at a wedding; from perfectly executed old fashions to ice cold martinis and our favorite craft beers. The management team made it known that they were available to us should we need anything at all during the evening and we felt extremely well taken care of. I really and truly could go on and on, but I'm sure at this point the only people still reading this post are that of Jude, Chef Piper and the other wonderful One North staff. Thank you Thank you Thank you for making the most important day of our lives memorable, beautiful and perfect. - Taylor and Brendan

It was one of the last warm days of October so we sat outside and it was simply perfect.  You get a great view of the Lyric Opera theater and this is a great place for dinner before the shows.  They even offer bar specials for theater patrons.  Both dishes we ordered were phenomenal - the sauteed calamari was full of flavor and meat and the risotto, mmm it was melt in your mouth kind of heaven.  Plus, you can't go wrong with bacon in risotto.
We were seated at noon. I sat there with my husband for 15 minutes and watched everyone around us get service. I won't be making that mistake again.

One North is one of my favorite places to eat when I am stuck in the loop after a long day. The menu is good, the service is great, and you are bound to find a bunch of people having a laugh for happy hour. Bring your friends. One north is very warm and inviting.

Power-Lunch only for the thick-skinned ... Came for lunch at 11:40 am, nobody around. Were shown the worst seating, told that the restaurant was booked (it wasn't); took some arguing to get better seating in empty place. Clearly, front-of-house managers don't empower their staff to be friendly and welcoming. It's not the staff's fault - it's clearly management.  Then, for being seated first, it took nearly 1 hour for food to arrive. That did not make any sense.  Some of the food was ok; tacos were completely impractical and not a good combination of tastes.  I can not recommend this place.

I was recently at One North Kitchen & Bar to send a co-worker off into Stay-at-Home-Mom Land. I was the one to make the reservation and the confirm the final number. Everyone I spoke to was very helpful and courteous.  They have a nice selection of liquor, beers and special drinks. As far as food, the crispy tater tots were a big hit with our crowd. The buffalo chicken sliders, not so much.  The service was great, our waiter was constantly checking on us, but not to the point of it being too much.  It would be a great place to grab a meal or drink before the Opera which is conveniently right across the street.

Came here for the first time for dinner during Restaurant Week. Had to specifically ask for the restaurant week menu, but the portions were great and the food was delicious. We had theater tickets, and the service was paced well. Also came here for lunch during the workday - great service and great lunch options.
There is nothing extremely special about this place, but I have always enjoyed the food. The salad and fish tacos are pretty good. It's conveniently close to offices in the loop.
Lovely atmosphere and great service  It's a wonderful mix of cutting edge modern decor and casual fine dining.
great option for happy hour after work in the loop

This spot is great! A bit expensive but the food and drinks are great. For a spot of town which is only filled with tons of lunch eateries, One North is a cool get away! Flatbread, red wines, and brussel sprouts are delicious!

I will NOT be returning….Caution!  I visited the restaurant and parked my car with the valet. When finished I retrieved my car and drove home, only to find $4 in coins missing from the retractable ash tray in my dashboard.  I called the restaurant and spoke to Tom, apparently the manager on duty. I explained what happened and he immediately replied “that’s unheard of!” – his response was so odd, as if I told him the sky was falling! Then he put me on hold for several minutes and came back on the line to say that he will call me back the next day once he investigated.  It is a week later and I have not heard from anyone.  One North will also not be seeing me again at their venues. Awful customer service.

I went there a few months ago for a lunch meeting.  It is a perfect place to meet as it is located at the beginning of the loop. I am not rushing back there for dinner. The food was good, but not exceptional.

Great atmosphere, incredible cuisine and outstanding beer on tap selection!  I'd highly recommend it for a nice treat yourself meal, casual cocktail on the patio or especially a visit before the Opera.
